  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$X.shape = (m, n), \\ y = \\sum\\limits_{i, j} 2 \\cdot x_{i, j} \\Rightarrow \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial x_{i, j}} = 2 \\Rightarrow \\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial X} = 2 \\cdot \\mathbb{1}_{m, n}, \\ $ где $\\mathbb{1}_{m, n} = \\left( 1\\right)_{i, j = 1}^{m, n}$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 71,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "y.backward()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x = torch.randint(-5, 5, size=(5, 3)).float()\n",
    "# При обратном проходе нужно вычислять градиенты по x\n",
    "x.requires_grad = True\n",
    "y = torch.trace(torch.matmul(x.t(), x))\n",
    "y"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$y = tr(X^T X) \\Rightarrow Dy[\\Delta X] = tr((\\nabla_{X}y)^T \\Delta X) = tr(X^T \\Delta X + \\Delta X^T X) = tr(2X^T \\Delta X) \\Rightarrow \\boxed{ \\nabla_{X}y = 2 \\cdot X } $"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 95,

    "$y = \\frac{1}{2} \\Vert Ax + b \\Vert_{2}^2 \\Rightarrow \\boxed{\\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial A} = \\nabla_{A} y = (Ax + b)x^{T}}, \\ \\boxed{\\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial b} = \\nabla_{b} y = Ax + b}$"
   ]
  },

    "### Задача 1 из семинара"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 148,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Image object>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 148,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from IPython.display import Image\n",
    "Image(filename='/Users/tony/Desktop/neural_nets_1.png') "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Для данного графа вычислений найдём производные выхода (y) по всем параметрам ($b_{1, 2}, \\ c_{1, 2}$)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$z_{1} = x_{1} + b_{1}, \\quad \\frac{\\partial z_{1}}{\\partial b_{1}} = 1$\n",
    "\n",
    "$z_{2} = x_{2} + b_{2}, \\quad \\frac{\\partial z_{2}}{\\partial b_{2}} = 1$\n",
    "\n",
    "$z_{3} = \\sigma(z_{1}), \\quad \\frac{\\partial z_{3}}{\\partial b_{1}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{3}}{\\partial z_{1}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{1}}{\\partial b_{1}} = \\sigma(z_{1})^{\\prime}_{z_{1}} \\cdot 1 = \\sigma(z_{1}) \\cdot \\left(1 - \\sigma(z_{1})\\right)$\n",
    "\n",
    "$z_{4} = \\sigma(z_{2}), \\quad \\frac{\\partial z_{4}}{\\partial b_{2}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{4}}{\\partial z_{2}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{2}}{\\partial b_{2}} = \\sigma(z_{2})^{\\prime}_{z_{2}} \\cdot 1 = \\sigma(z_{2}) \\cdot \\left(1 - \\sigma(z_{2})\\right)$\n",
    "\n",
    "$z_{5} = \\tanh(z_{2}), \\quad \\frac{\\partial z_{5}}{\\partial b_{2}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{5}}{\\partial z_{2}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{2}}{\\partial b_{2}} = \\tanh(z_{2})^{\\prime}_{z_{2}} \\cdot 1 = 1 - \\tanh(z_{2})^2$\n",
    "\n",
    "$z_{6} = c_{2} \\cdot z_{5}, \\quad \\frac{\\partial z_{6}}{\\partial c_{2}} = z_{5}, \\ \\frac{\\partial z_{6}}{\\partial b_{2}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{6}}{\\partial z_{5}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{5}}{\\partial z_{2}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{2}}{\\partial b_{2}} = c_{2} \\cdot \\tanh(z_{2})^{\\prime}_{z_{2}} \\cdot 1 = c_{2} \\cdot \\left(1 - \\tanh(z_{2})^2 \\right)$\n",
    "\n",
    "$z_{7} = z_{4} \\cdot z_{1}, \\quad \\frac{\\partial z_{7}}{\\partial b_{1}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{7}}{\\partial z_{1}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{1}}{\\partial b_{1}} = z_{4} \\cdot 1, \\ \\frac{\\partial z_{7}}{\\partial b_{2}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{7}}{\\partial z_{4}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{4}}{\\partial z_{2}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{2}}{\\partial b_{2}} = z_{1} \\cdot \\sigma(z_{2})^{\\prime}_{z_{2}} \\cdot 1 = z_{1} \\cdot \\sigma(z_{2}) \\cdot \\left(1 - \\sigma(z_{2})\\right)$\n",
    "\n",
    "$z_{8} = z_{7} \\cdot c_{1}, \\quad \\frac{\\partial z_{8}}{\\partial c_{1}} = z_{7}, \\ \\frac{\\partial z_{8}}{\\partial b_{1}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{8}}{\\partial z_{7}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{7}}{\\partial z_{1}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{1}}{\\partial b_{1}} = c_{1} \\cdot z_{4} \\cdot 1, \\ \\frac{\\partial z_{8}}{\\partial b_{2}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{8}}{\\partial z_{7}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{7}}{\\partial z_{4}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{4}}{\\partial z_{2}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{2}}{\\partial b_{2}} = c_{1} \\cdot z_{1} \\cdot \\sigma(z_{2})^{\\prime}_{z_{2}} \\cdot 1 = c_{1} \\cdot z_{1} \\cdot \\sigma(z_{2}) \\cdot \\left(1 - \\sigma(z_{2}) \\right)$\n",
    "\n",
    "$z_{9} = z_{3} \\cdot z_{6}, \\quad \\frac{\\partial z_{9}}{\\partial b_{1}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{9}}{\\partial z_{3}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{3}}{\\partial z_{1}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{1}}{\\partial b_{1}} = z_{6} \\cdot \\sigma(z_{1})^{\\prime}_{z_{1}} \\cdot 1, \\ \\frac{\\partial z_{9}}{\\partial c_{2}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{9}}{\\partial z_{6}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{6}}{\\partial c_{2}} = z_{3} \\cdot z_{5}, \\ \\frac{\\partial z_{9}}{\\partial b_{2}} = \\frac{\\partial z_{9}}{\\partial z_{6}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{6}}{\\partial z_{5}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{5}}{\\partial z_{2}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_{2}}{\\partial b_{2}} = z_{3} \\cdot c_{2} \\cdot \\tanh(z_{2})^{\\prime}_{z_{2}} \\cdot 1$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Формула, по которой производится вычисление y выглядит следующим образом: \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "$$y = z_{8} + z_{9} = \\sigma(x_{2} + b_{2}) \\cdot (x_{1} + b_{1}) \\cdot c_{1} + \\sigma(x_{1} + b_{1}) \\cdot c_{2} \\cdot \\tanh(x_{2} + b_{2})$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$\\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial c_{1}} = \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial c_{1}} (c_{1} \\cdot z_{8}) = z_{8} = $"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 177,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "True\n",
      "True\n",
      "True\n",
      "True\n",
      "\n",
      "False\n",
      "False\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x1 = torch.FloatTensor([2])\n",
    "x2 = torch.FloatTensor([-0.7])\n",
    "b1 = torch.FloatTensor([0.3])\n",
    "b1.requires_grad = True\n",
    "b2 = torch.FloatTensor([0.01])\n",
    "b2.requires_grad = True\n",
    "c1 = torch.FloatTensor([-1])\n",
    "c1.requires_grad = True\n",
    "c2 = torch.FloatTensor([-5])\n",
    "c2.requires_grad = True\n",
    "for i in [b1, b2, c1, c2]:\n",
    "    print(i.requires_grad)\n",
    "print()\n",
    "for i in [x1, x2]:\n",
    "    print(i.requires_grad)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 178,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "params = {'b1': b1, 'b2': b2, 'c1': c1, 'c2': c2}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 179,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "tensor([1.9492], grad_fn=<AddBackward0>)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 179,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "y = c2 * torch.sigmoid(x1 + b1) * torch.tanh(x2 + b2) + c1 * (x1 + b1) * torch.sigmoid(x2 + b2)\n",
    "y"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 180,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "y.backward()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 182,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b1 tensor([-0.0864])\n",
      "b2 tensor([-3.4310])\n",
      "c1 tensor([0.7683])\n",
      "c2 tensor([-0.5435])\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for param in params:\n",
    "    print(param, params[param].grad)"
   ]
  },

    "Пример данных"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [

     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [

    "train_ids, val_ids, test_ids = np.split(\n",
    "    np.arange(data.shape[0]), [split1, split2]\n",

    "BATCH_SIZE = 100\n",
    "train_iterator = DataLoader(torch.FloatTensor(data[train_ids]), \n",
    "                            batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)\n",
    "val_iterator = DataLoader(torch.FloatTensor(data[val_ids]), \n",
    "                          batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class FFNet(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, input_dim, layer1, layer2, layer3, layer4, layer5, output_dim):\n",
    "        super(FFNet, self).__init__()\n",
    "        self.hid_0_1 = nn.Linear(input_dim, layer1)\n",
    "        self.hid_1_2 = nn.Linear(layer1, layer2)\n",
    "        self.hid_2_out = nn.Linear(layer2, output_dim)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        out = F.relu(self.hid_0_1(x))\n",
    "        out = F.relu(self.hid_1_2(out))\n",
    "        out = self.hid_2_out(out)\n",
    "        return out"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "INPUT_DIM = OUTPUT_DIM = data.shape[1] - 1\n",
    "DEVICE = 'cuda'\n",
    "TRAIN_BATCHES_LEN, VAL_BATCHES_LEN = int(np.floor(len(train_ids)/BATCH_SIZE)), int(np.floor(len(val_ids)/BATCH_SIZE))"
   ]
  },

    "                    output_dim=10)\n",
    "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
    "opt = optim.Adam(params=model.parameters(), lr=1e-4)"

   ],
   "source": [
    "EPOCHS = 100\n",
    "model.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "criterion.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "train_loss = []\n",
    "val_loss = []\n",
    "for epoch in tqdm(range(1, EPOCHS + 1)):\n",
    "    st = time.perf_counter()\n",
    "    model.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "    current_loss = 0\n",
    "    model.train()\n",
    "    for batch in train_iterator:\n",
    "        opt.zero_grad()\n",
    "        x, y = batch[:, :-1].to(DEVICE), batch[:, -1].type(torch.LongTensor).to(DEVICE)\n",
    "        y_pred = model(x)\n",
    "        loss = criterion(y_pred, y)\n",
    "        loss.backward()\n",
    "        opt.step()\n",
    "        current_loss += loss.item()/TRAIN_BATCHES_LEN\n",
    "    train_loss.append(current_loss)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    model.eval()\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        current_loss = 0\n",
    "        for batch in val_iterator:\n",
    "            x, y = batch[:, :-1].to(DEVICE), batch[:, -1].type(torch.LongTensor).to(DEVICE)\n",
    "            y_pred = model(x)\n",
    "            loss = criterion(y_pred, y)\n",
    "            current_loss += loss.item()/VAL_BATCHES_LEN\n",
    "        val_loss.append(current_loss)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    torch.save(model.cpu().state_dict(), 'epoch{}'.format(epoch))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print('Epoch: {}'.format(epoch), 'train loss: {:.3f}'.format(train_loss[-1]), \n",
    "         'val loss: {:.3f}'.format(val_loss[-1]), 'Time: {}'.format(time.perf_counter() - st))"
   ]
  },

    "### Снижение размерности с помощью автокодировкщика"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "split1, split2 = int(np.floor(data.shape[0]*0.6)), int(np.floor(data.shape[0]*0.85))\n",
    "train_ids, val_ids, test_ids = np.split(\n",
    "    np.arange(data.shape[0]), [split1, split2]\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "BATCH_SIZE = 100\n",
    "train_iterator = DataLoader(torch.FloatTensor(data[train_ids]), \n",
    "                            batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)\n",
    "val_iterator = DataLoader(torch.FloatTensor(data[val_ids]), \n",
    "                          batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 140,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class AutoEncoder(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, input_dim, layer1, layer2, layer3, layer4, layer5, output_dim):\n",
    "        super(AutoEncoder, self).__init__()\n",
    "        self.hid_0_1 = nn.Linear(input_dim, layer1)\n",
    "        self.hid_1_2 = nn.Linear(layer1, layer2)\n",
    "        self.hid_2_3 = nn.Linear(layer2, layer3)\n",
    "        self.hid_3_4 = nn.Linear(layer3, layer4)\n",
    "        self.hid_4_5 = nn.Linear(layer4, layer5)\n",
    "        self.hid_5_out = nn.Linear(layer5, output_dim)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def encode(self, x):\n",
    "        out = F.relu(self.hid_0_1(x))\n",
    "        out = F.relu(self.hid_1_2(out))\n",
    "        out = self.hid_2_3(out)\n",
    "        return out\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def decode(self, x):\n",
    "        out = F.relu(self.hid_3_4(F.relu(x)))\n",
    "        out = F.relu(self.hid_4_5(out))\n",
    "        out = self.hid_5_out(out)\n",
    "        return out"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 174,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "INPUT_DIM = OUTPUT_DIM = data.shape[1] - 1\n",
    "DEVICE = 'cuda'\n",
    "TRAIN_BATCHES_LEN, VAL_BATCHES_LEN = int(np.floor(len(train_ids)/BATCH_SIZE)), int(np.floor(len(val_ids)/BATCH_SIZE))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 175,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model = AutoEncoder(input_dim=INPUT_DIM, layer1=300, layer2=100, layer3=2, layer4=100, layer5=300, \n",
    "                    output_dim=OUTPUT_DIM)\n",
    "criterion = nn.MSELoss()\n",
    "opt = optim.Adam(params=model.parameters(), lr=1e-4)"
   ]
  },

      "Epoch: 98 train loss: 2678.484 val loss: 2791.009 Time: 4.6615164573304355\n",
      "Epoch: 99 train loss: 2679.473 val loss: 2791.237 Time: 4.36073977407068\n",
      "Epoch: 100 train loss: 2676.565 val loss: 2796.208 Time: 4.043359046801925\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "EPOCHS = 100\n",
    "model.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "criterion.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "train_loss = []\n",
    "val_loss = []\n",
    "for epoch in tqdm(range(1, EPOCHS + 1)):\n",
    "    st = time.perf_counter()\n",
    "    model.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "    current_loss = 0\n",
    "    model.train()\n",
    "    for batch in train_iterator:\n",
    "        opt.zero_grad()\n",
    "        x, y = batch[:, :-1].to(DEVICE), batch[:, -1].reshape(-1, 1)\n",
    "        x_encode = model.encode(x)\n",
    "        x_reconstructed = model.decode(x_encode)\n",
    "        loss = criterion(x_reconstructed, x)\n",
    "        loss.backward()\n",
    "        opt.step()\n",
    "        current_loss += loss.item()/TRAIN_BATCHES_LEN\n",
    "    train_loss.append(current_loss)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    model.eval()\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        current_loss = 0\n",
    "        for batch in val_iterator:\n",
    "            x, y = batch[:, :-1].to(DEVICE), batch[:, -1].reshape(-1, 1)\n",
    "            x_encode = model.encode(x)\n",
    "            x_reconstructed = model.decode(x_encode)\n",
    "            loss = criterion(x_reconstructed, x)\n",
    "            current_loss += loss.item()/VAL_BATCHES_LEN\n",
    "        val_loss.append(current_loss)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    torch.save(model.cpu().state_dict(), 'epoch{}'.format(epoch))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print('Epoch: {}'.format(epoch), 'train loss: {:.3f}'.format(train_loss[-1]), \n",
    "         'val loss: {:.3f}'.format(val_loss[-1]), 'Time: {}'.format(time.perf_counter() - st))"
   ]
  },

    "from scipy.signal import convolve2d"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 279,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "granzes = np.array([[ -3-3j, 0-10j,  +3 -3j],\n",
    "          [-10+0j, 0+ 0j, +10 +0j],\n",
    "                    [ -3+3j, 0+10j,  +3 +3j]])\n",
    "\n",
    "sharpen = np.array([\n",
    "    [1, 1, 1],\n",
    "    [1, -8, 1],\n",
    "    [1, 1, 1]\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "sobel = np.array([\n",
    "    [-1, -2, -1],\n",
    "    [0, 0, 0],\n",
    "    [1, 2, 1]\n",
    "])"
   ]
  },

    "image_conv1 = convolve2d(image_pixels[..., 0], granzes, boundary='symm', mode='same')\n",

    "image_conv3 = convolve2d(image_pixels[..., 0], sobel, boundary='symm', mode='same')"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Свёртки в pytorch"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 283,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# nn.Conv2d(\n",
    "#     in_channels - количество входных каналов у изображения (у нашего RGB, то есть 3 канала)\n",
    "#     out_channels - количество выходных каналов после применения свёртки\n",
    "#     kernel_size - размер применяемой свёртки ( 3 х 3 например)\n",
    "#     padding - сколько добавлять нулей после границы изображения:\n",
    "#     Пример:\n",
    "#            padding = 2 ->   0000000\n",
    "#                             0000000\n",
    "#                             0012300\n",
    "#                             0045600\n",
    "#                             0078900\n",
    "#                             0000000\n",
    "#                             0000000\n",
    "#     stride - c каким шагом перемещать свёртку.\n",
    "#     dilation - увеличивает область зависимости свёртки\n",
    "# )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 284,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# expand - добавляем размерность BATCH_SIZE и назначаем её равно 1. permute - отправляем каналы (RGB) на 2 размерность\n",
    "X = torch.FloatTensor(image_pixels).expand(size=[1, 100, 100, 3]).permute(0, 3, 1, 2)\n",
    "kernel = nn.Conv2d(in_channels=3, out_channels=1, kernel_size=(3, 3), bias=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 285,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "kernel.weight.data = torch.FloatTensor([[\n",
    "    [[-1, -1, -1],\n",
    "     [-1, 8, -1],\n",
    "     [-1, -1, -1]],\n",
    "    \n",
    "    [[-1, -1, -1],\n",
    "     [-1, 8, -1],\n",
    "     [-1, -1, -1]],\n",
    "    \n",
    "    [[-1, -1, -1],\n",
    "     [-1, 8, -1],\n",
    "     [-1, -1, -1]]\n",
    "]])"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "#### Обучение свёрточной нейросети"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "split1, split2 = int(np.floor(data.shape[0]*0.6)), int(np.floor(data.shape[0]*0.85))\n",
    "train_ids, val_ids, test_ids = np.split(\n",
    "    np.arange(data.shape[0]), [split1, split2]\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "BATCH_SIZE = 128\n",
    "N_TRAIN_BATCHES = len(train_ids)/BATCH_SIZE\n",
    "N_VAL_BATCHES = len(val_ids)/BATCH_SIZE\n",
    "train_iterator = DataLoader(torch.FloatTensor(data[train_ids]), \n",
    "                            batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)\n",
    "val_iterator = DataLoader(torch.FloatTensor(data[val_ids]), \n",
    "                          batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class ConvNet(nn.Module):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(\n",
    "         self, \n",
    "         out_channels1=10, \n",
    "         out_channels2=10, \n",
    "         kernel1=(4, 4), \n",
    "         kernel2=(4, 4), \n",
    "         pool_kernel1=(2, 2),\n",
    "         pool_kernel2=(2, 2),\n",
    "         output_dim=10\n",
    "):\n",
    "        super(ConvNet, self).__init__()\n",
    "        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(in_channels=1, out_channels=out_channels1, kernel_size=kernel1)\n",
    "        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(in_channels=out_channels1, out_channels=out_channels2, kernel_size=kernel2)\n",
    "        self.pool_kernel1 = pool_kernel1\n",
    "        self.pool_kernel2 = pool_kernel2\n",
    "        # Вычисляем размер выхода после первой свёртки и макспуллинга\n",
    "        after_1_maxpool = ((28 - (kernel1[0] - 1) - 1) + 1)//pool_kernel1[0]\n",
    "        # Вычисляем размер выхода после второй свёртки и макспуллинга\n",
    "        after_2_maxpool = ((after_1_maxpool - (kernel2[0] - 1) - 1) + 1)//pool_kernel2[0]\n",
    "        last_layer_input_dim = out_channels2*after_2_maxpool**2\n",
    "        self.last_layer = nn.Linear(in_features=last_layer_input_dim, \n",
    "                                    out_features=output_dim)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        out = F.max_pool2d(self.conv1(x.expand(1, *x.shape).permute(1, 0, 2).view(x.shape[0], 1, 28, 28)), \n",
    "                           kernel_size=self.pool_kernel1)\n",
    "        out = F.max_pool2d(self.conv2(out), kernel_size=self.pool_kernel2)\n",
    "        out = self.last_layer(out.view(x.shape[0], -1))\n",
    "        return out"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "convnet_model = ConvNet()\n",
    "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
    "opt = optim.Adam(convnet_model.parameters(), lr=1e-4)"
   ]
  },

      "Epoch: 98 train loss: 0.025 val loss: 0.116 Time: 1.5448398280059337\n",
      "Epoch: 99 train loss: 0.025 val loss: 0.116 Time: 1.5372549859966966\n",
      "Epoch: 100 train loss: 0.025 val loss: 0.114 Time: 1.5459757150019868\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "DEVICE = 'cuda'\n",
    "EPOCHS = 100\n",
    "convnet_model.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "criterion.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "train_loss = []\n",
    "val_loss = []\n",
    "for epoch in tqdm_notebook(range(1, EPOCHS + 1)):\n",
    "    st = time.perf_counter()\n",
    "    convnet_model.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "    current_loss = 0\n",
    "    convnet_model.train()\n",
    "    for batch in train_iterator:\n",
    "        opt.zero_grad()\n",
    "        x, y = batch[:, :-1].to(DEVICE), batch[:, -1].long().to(DEVICE)\n",
    "        y_pred = convnet_model(x)\n",
    "        loss = criterion(y_pred, y)\n",
    "        loss.backward()\n",
    "        opt.step()\n",
    "        current_loss += loss.item()/N_TRAIN_BATCHES\n",
    "    train_loss.append(current_loss)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    convnet_model.eval()\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        current_loss = 0\n",
    "        for batch in val_iterator:\n",
    "            x, y = batch[:, :-1].to(DEVICE), batch[:, -1].long().to(DEVICE)\n",
    "            y_pred = convnet_model(x)\n",
    "            loss = criterion(y_pred, y)\n",
    "            current_loss += loss.item()/N_VAL_BATCHES\n",
    "        val_loss.append(current_loss)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    torch.save(convnet_model.cpu().state_dict(), 'epoch{}'.format(epoch))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print('Epoch: {}'.format(epoch), 'train loss: {:.3f}'.format(train_loss[-1]), \n",
    "         'val loss: {:.3f}'.format(val_loss[-1]), 'Time: {}'.format(time.perf_counter() - st))"
   ]
  },

    "DEVICE = 'cuda'\n",
    "BATCH_SIZE = 4"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Data augmentation and normalization for training\n",
    "# Just normalization for validation\n",
    "data_transforms = {\n",
    "    'train': transforms.Compose([\n",
    "        transforms.RandomResizedCrop(224),\n",
    "        transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(),\n",
    "        transforms.ToTensor(),\n",
    "        transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225])\n",
    "    ]),\n",
    "    'val': transforms.Compose([\n",
    "        transforms.Resize(256),\n",
    "        transforms.CenterCrop(224),\n",
    "        transforms.ToTensor(),\n",
    "        transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225])\n",
    "    ]),\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "image_datasets = {x: datasets.ImageFolder(x,\n",
    "                                          data_transforms[x])\n",
    "                  for x in ['train', 'val']}\n",
    "dataloaders = {x: torch.utils.data.DataLoader(image_datasets[x], batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,\n",
    "                                             shuffle=True, num_workers=4)\n",
    "              for x in ['train', 'val']}\n",
    "dataset_sizes = {x: len(image_datasets[x]) for x in ['train', 'val']}\n",
    "# 0 - муравьи, 1 - пчёлы\n",
    "class_names = image_datasets['train'].classes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 106,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "torch.Size([4, 3, 224, 224])\n",
      "tensor([1, 1, 0, 0])\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Посмотрим на примеры данных\n",
    "for dat in dataloaders['train']:\n",
    "    x = dat\n",
    "    break\n",
    "    \n",
    "print(x[0].shape) # размер батча, число каналов, высота изображения, ширина изображения \n",
    "print(x[1])"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 108,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x864 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# стандартные параметры для правильного отображения картинки\n",
    "mean = np.array([0.485, 0.456, 0.406]) \n",
    "std = np.array([0.229, 0.224, 0.225])\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=2, figsize=(12, 12))\n",
    "for n, i in enumerate(itertools.product(range(2), range(2))):\n",
    "    inp = std * (x[0][n]).numpy().transpose((1, 2, 0)) + mean\n",
    "    target = 'ant' if x[1][n].item() == 0 else 'bee'\n",
    "    inp = np.clip(inp, 0, 1)\n",
    "    ax[i].set_title(target, fontsize=15);\n",
    "    ax[i].imshow(inp);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 121,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def train_model(model, criterion, optimizer, scheduler, num_epochs=25):\n",
    "    since = time.time()\n",
    "\n",
    "    best_model_wts = copy.deepcopy(model.state_dict())\n",
    "    best_acc = 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "    for epoch in range(num_epochs):\n",
    "        print('Epoch {}/{}'.format(epoch, num_epochs - 1))\n",
    "        print('-' * 10)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Each epoch has a training and validation phase\n",
    "        for phase in ['train', 'val']:\n",
    "            if phase == 'train':\n",
    "                model.train()  # Set model to training mode\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                model.eval()   # Set model to evaluate mode\n",
    "\n",
    "            running_loss = 0.0\n",
    "            running_corrects = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Iterate over data.\n",
    "            for inputs, labels in dataloaders[phase]:\n",
    "                inputs = inputs.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "                labels = labels.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "\n",
    "                # zero the parameter gradients\n",
    "                optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "\n",
    "                # forward\n",
    "                # track history if only in train\n",
    "                with torch.set_grad_enabled(phase == 'train'):\n",
    "                    outputs = model(inputs)\n",
    "                    _, preds = torch.max(outputs, 1)\n",
    "                    loss = criterion(outputs, labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "                    # backward + optimize only if in training phase\n",
    "                    if phase == 'train':\n",
    "                        loss.backward()\n",
    "                        optimizer.step()\n",
    "\n",
    "                # statistics\n",
    "                running_loss += loss.item() * inputs.size(0)\n",
    "                running_corrects += torch.sum(preds == labels.data)\n",
    "            if phase == 'train':\n",
    "                scheduler.step()\n",
    "\n",
    "            epoch_loss = running_loss / dataset_sizes[phase]\n",
    "            epoch_acc = running_corrects.double() / dataset_sizes[phase]\n",
    "\n",
    "            print('{} Loss: {:.4f} Acc: {:.4f}'.format(\n",
    "                phase, epoch_loss, epoch_acc))\n",
    "\n",
    "            # deep copy the model\n",
    "            if phase == 'val' and epoch_acc > best_acc:\n",
    "                best_acc = epoch_acc\n",
    "                best_model_wts = copy.deepcopy(model.state_dict())\n",
    "\n",
    "        print()\n",
    "\n",
    "    time_elapsed = time.time() - since\n",
    "    print('Training complete in {:.0f}m {:.0f}s'.format(\n",
    "        time_elapsed // 60, time_elapsed % 60))\n",
    "    print('Best val Acc: {:4f}'.format(best_acc))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # load best model weights\n",
    "    model.load_state_dict(best_model_wts)\n",
    "    return model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 122,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def visualize_model(model, num_images=6):\n",
    "    was_training = model.training\n",
    "    model.eval()\n",
    "    images_so_far = 0\n",
    "    fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        for i, (inputs, labels) in enumerate(dataloaders['val']):\n",
    "            inputs = inputs.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "            labels = labels.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "\n",
    "            outputs = model(inputs)\n",
    "            _, preds = torch.max(outputs, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "            for j in range(inputs.size()[0]):\n",
    "                images_so_far += 1\n",
    "                ax = plt.subplot(num_images//2, 2, images_so_far)\n",
    "                ax.axis('off')\n",
    "                ax.set_title('predicted: {}'.format(class_names[preds[j]]))\n",
    "                imshow(inputs.cpu().data[j])\n",
    "\n",
    "                if images_so_far == num_images:\n",
    "                    model.train(mode=was_training)\n",
    "                    return\n",
    "        model.train(mode=was_training)\n"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 123,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model_ft = models.resnet18(pretrained=True)\n",
    "num_ftrs = model_ft.fc.in_features\n",
    "# Here the size of each output sample is set to 2.\n",
    "# Alternatively, it can be generalized to nn.Linear(num_ftrs, len(class_names)).\n",
    "model_ft.fc = nn.Linear(num_ftrs, 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "model_ft = model_ft.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "\n",
    "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Observe that all parameters are being optimized\n",
    "optimizer_ft = optim.SGD(model_ft.parameters(), lr=0.001, momentum=0.9)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Decay LR by a factor of 0.1 every 7 epochs\n",
    "exp_lr_scheduler = optim.lr_scheduler.StepLR(optimizer_ft, step_size=7, gamma=0.1)"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",

    {
     "data": {

    "visualize_model(model_ft)"

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 128,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model_conv = torchvision.models.resnet18(pretrained=True)\n",
    "for param in model_conv.parameters():\n",
    "    param.requires_grad = False\n",
    "\n",
    "# Parameters of newly constructed modules have requires_grad=True by default\n",
    "num_ftrs = model_conv.fc.in_features\n",
    "model_conv.fc = nn.Linear(num_ftrs, 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "model_conv = model_conv.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "\n",
    "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Observe that only parameters of final layer are being optimized as\n",
    "# opposed to before.\n",
    "optimizer_conv = optim.SGD(model_conv.fc.parameters(), lr=0.001, momentum=0.9)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Decay LR by a factor of 0.1 every 7 epochs\n",
    "exp_lr_scheduler = optim.lr_scheduler.StepLR(optimizer_conv, step_size=7, gamma=0.1)"
   ]
  },
